 I was a lonely woman who was in love with a dog. I picked up an abused, abandoned puppy from the pound who was not a very good fit for me at all. The first time I laid eyes on him, he growled and lunged at me. But I took him for a walk and he hesitated for a few moments before lunging again. So I decided to take him home anyway. I named him Leonidas and he needed some serious behavioral training to make him more dog
